HEADWORD: Astray
<hw>A*stray"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv. & a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Estray</er>, <er>Stray</er>.]</ety> <def>Out of the right, either in
a literal or in a figurative sense; wandering; <as>as, to lead one
<ex>astray</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye were as sheep going <qex>astray</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Pet. ii.
25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Astrict</ent>⟦br⟧
